==English==
''1920s slang, now archaic''

===Etymology===
[[Russian]] [[дворник]] "concierge; one who takes care of the pavement and yard in front of a house", from [[двор]] "courtyard"

===Noun===
'''dvornik'''
# a [[doorman]] or domestic [[porter]], usually at an upscale apartment building
#:''Freddie was ejected by the '''dvornik''' after making a scene.''

